stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> Registered: register() → IdentityRegistered (credential stored as salted hash)
  Registered --> Authenticated: authenticate() ok → Authenticated + SessionCreated
  Registered --> Rejected: authenticate() bad creds → AuthenticationFailed
  Rejected --> Registered: retry with correct credentials
  Authenticated --> Refreshed: refresh() (token-validated) → SessionRefreshed
  Refreshed --> Refreshed: refresh() again (extends lease)
  Authenticated --> Expired: now ≥ expiresAt (settled on access)
  Refreshed --> Expired: lease elapsed
  Authenticated --> Revoked: revoke() → SessionRevoked
  Refreshed --> Revoked: revoke()
  Expired --> Authenticated: re-authenticate → new session
  Revoked --> Authenticated: re-authenticate → new session

  note right of Authenticated
    resolve({ sessionId }) → { ok: isLive, context }
    resolve({ principal }) → context only (authenticated:false)
    The frozen authorization context (roles/permissions/claims/tenant)
    is what the Policy engine (ADR-025) evaluates. Tokens/credentials
    never appear in events, the SDK, or API responses.
  end note
